## Creation via Content Browser

**Blueprints** are stored in packages and can be created through the **Content Browser** like any other asset.

[EXCERPT:CreateBP1]

[REGION:raw]
![](CreateBP_mainFlow.png)
[/REGION]

1. In the **Content Browser**, click on ![Create Asset Button](button_new_asset_blueprint.png).

1. Select **Blueprint** under the _Create Basic Asset_ section from the menu that appears.

	[REGION:note]
	Additional [](Engine/Blueprints/UserGuide/Types) can be created from the **Blueprints** option under _Create Advanced Asset_. 
	[/REGION]

1. Choose a **Parent Class** for your _Blueprint_.

	![Choose a Parent Class](new_asset_parent_class.png)

	[REGION:note]
	See [Parent Classes](Engine\Blueprints\UserGuide\Types\ClassBlueprint#parentclasses) for info on selecting a Parent Class. 
	[/REGION]
	
[/EXCERPT:CreateBP1]
	

## Right-click Creation

There are two other methods in which you can create a **Blueprint** from the **Content Browser**.

[EXCERPT:CreateBP2]

1. **Right-click** in the **Asset View** (right-hand panel) of the **Content Browser**. 

1. Select **Blueprint** under the _Create Basic Asset_ section from the menu that appears.

	[REGION:raw]
	![New Asset menu](new_asset_blueprint_menu.png)
	[/REGION]

1. Choose a **Parent Class** for your _Blueprint_.

	![Choose a Parent Class](new_asset_parent_class.png)

	[REGION:note]
	See [Parent Classes](Engine\Blueprints\UserGuide\Types\ClassBlueprint#parentclasses) for info on selecting a Parent Class. 
	[/REGION]

[/EXCERPT:CreateBP2]

Alternatively:

[EXCERPT:CreateBP3]

1. **Right-click** on a folder in the **Asset Tree** (left-hand panel) of the **Content Browser**.

1. In the menu that appears, mouse over **Create Asset** then select **Blueprint**.

	[REGION:raw]
	![](rtclick_content_browser_asset_tree.png)
	[/REGION]

1. Choose a **Parent Class** for your _Blueprint_.

	![Choose a Parent Class](new_asset_parent_class.png)

	[REGION:note]
	See [Parent Classes](Engine\Blueprints\UserGuide\Types\ClassBlueprint#parentclasses) for info on selecting a Parent Class. 
	[/REGION]

[/EXCERPT:CreateBP3]

