##Creation via Class Viewer

When creating Blueprints via the [Class Viewer](Engine/UI/ClassViewer), it can be helpful to first filter the displayed classes to _Blueprint_ bases only. 

1. In the **Class Viewer** toolbar, click on **Filters**.

	![](class_viewer_filters.png)

1. In the **Filters** menu, select **Blueprint Bases Only**.

	![](filter_blueprint_class_viewer.png)


Once you have filtered the list of classes, navigate to the class you would like to use as a base for your _Blueprint_. In the example here, we are creating a _Blueprint_ with a **CameraActor** as a base.

1. Click on the down arrow icon to the right of your chosen class. 

	![](class_viewer_arrow.png)

1. The option to **Create Blueprint** will appear. Click on this, and the dialog for creating a _Blueprint_ will appear.

	![](class_viewer_down_arrow.png)

1. Enter a name for your _Blueprint_, and select the folder where it should be saved.

1. Click on "Create [Path]/[Name]" at the top of the _Blueprint_ creation dialog, and your _Blueprint_ will be created and open in the **Blueprint Editor**.
	
	![](class_viewer_create_complete.png)

1. To save your _Blueprint_ in the Editor and complete the creation process, click on ![Save](blueprint_editor_save.png) in the **Blueprint Editor** toolbar.



You can also access _Blueprint_ creation in the **Class Viewer** by **right-clicking** directly on the class you would like to use as a base for your _Blueprint_. 
The _Blueprint_ creation process is the same as if you used the ![Down Arrow Icon](button_down_arrow.png) to the right of the class.

![](rtclick_class_viewer_bp.png)



